A Brazilian cameraman covering riots over bus far increases has been left braindead after being hit by an explosive device.

Santiago Andrade, 49, was filming the bloody confrontation near Rio de Janeiro's central station for the Band TV channel when he was hit by the projectile, thought to have been thrown by a protester.

He was pictured bleeding from the head after the dramatic incident on Thursday, which came as protesters furious about a 10-cent hike in bus fare clashed with police.

